    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Adee</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Confidential.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: During his interview with the second secretary
                    and Mr. Alexander, Waller stated that he had been subjected to cruel treatment
                    on board of the French steamer which brought him to France. He said that he was
                    chained to the floor by his arms and legs and was kept on his back in that
                    condition for seven days, and was exposed to gross indignities. As by the text
                    of your cable of the 22d instant instructions were to investigate all matters
                    connected with his trial, this statement was not included in Waller’s sworn
                    statement, but I communicate it for the information of the Department.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Eustis</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
